ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 7d shows the plot of degradation efficiency of PDM as a function of time with varying concentrations of CGGO. The pseudo-first-order rate kinetic model was applied to determine the rate constants from respective linear plots as shown in Fig. 7e, and the resultant rate constants are listed in Table 1
. The rate constant value increases with increasing concentrations of CGGO in which 60 μg/mL added CGGO exhibits a higher rate constant of 0.1448min−1. Moreover, the estimated rate constant (0.1448min−1) with CGGO is much higher than that obtained with other metal oxides-based photocatalysts including ZnO and TiO2 (Table 2
), demonstrating its effective catalytic capability towards PDM [57–60].
